This type of diabetes is typically diagnosed in children and young adults, and is often associated with obesity. Type 2 diabetes, on the other hand, is a metabolic disorder that is caused by insulin resistance and a relative insulin deficiency. This type of diabetes is typically diagnosed in adults and is often associated with obesity, physical inactivity, and a family history of the disease.
